text: Siikalatva is a municipality in Northern Ostrobothnia, Finland. As of 30 September 2023, 4,960 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Haapavesi, Kajaani, Kärsämäki, Liminka, Muhos, Pyhäntä, Raahe, Siikajoki and Vaala. It has four Lutheran churches. The former municipalities of Kestilä, Piippola, Pulkkila and Rantsila were merged into Siikalatva on 1 January 2009. == Other websites == * Municipality of Siikalatva – Official website Category:2009 establishments in Europe Category:2000s establishments in Finland Category:Municipalities of North Ostrobothnia
